  "doc_id": "32308",
  "text": "On the basis of previous studies showing a critical role of myeloid A2AAR signaling in attenuating renal ischemia reperfusion injury [CITATION_1] and the above results, we pursued the hypothesis that myeloid A2AAR signaling attenuates renal ischemia-reperfusion injury, while renal A2BAR signaling is important for preconditioning phenomena. For this purpose, we transplanted A2BAR À/À or A2BAR þ/þ mice with bone marrow from A2AAR À/À or A2AAR þ/þ mice. Consistent with the above hypothesis, these studies revealed that renoprotection by IP required renal A2BAR signaling, while mice without a myeloid A2AAR had more severe ischemia reperfusion injury ( Figure 11A and 11B).",
